   "steps":[
      {
         "id":"5e944116-64ae-466c-9b4f-61f62352791e",
         "title":{
            "en":"Teeth Ratio"
         },
         "text":{
            "en":"In this challenge you will learn about Teeth Ratio.<br/>Teeth Ratio expresses the relationship between the driver gear and the driven gear based on the number of teeth they have."
         },
         "type":"horizontal"
      },
      {
         "id":"a7c17d73-5459-4367-a3b6-10d8550e4a7f",
         "title":{
            "en":"Review"
         },
         "text":{
            "en":"When a driver gear is smaller than the driven grear, it increases torque and decreases speed."
         },
         "type":"horizontal"
      },
      {
         "id":"43025506-fa34-48ae-bd63-a645c3478161",
         "title":{
            "en":"Review"
         },
         "text":{
            "en":"When a driver gear is bigger than the driven gear, it decreases torque and increases speed."         
         },
         "type":"horizontal"
      },
      {
         "id":"f852c704-7afe-4e17-9350-988a0583be42",
         "title":{
            "en":"Teeth Ratio"
         },
         "text":{
            "en":"Teeth Ratio is calculated as:<br/>The number of teeth of the Driver Gear : The number of teeth of the Driven Gear"
         },
         "type":"horizontal"
      },
      {
         "id":"1718b19a-2429-44f8-a6a3-6febcf0b043d",
         "title":{
            "en":"Example"
         },
         "text":{
            "en":"If you have a 40-tooth driver gear and a 60-tooth driven gear, the Teeth Ratio is 40:60, or 2:3."
         },
         "type":"horizontal"
      },  
      {
      "id":"287d78db-9b70-4927-98c2-27da3ec4f494",
      "title":{
         "en":"Let us challenge you now!"
      },
      "text":{
         "en":""
